<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057071-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 8 and c = 9. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 3" class="text"/></p>
<p>
A = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <input type="text" style="width:25ch" name="qn1002" id="qn1002" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 3 of 3" class="text"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.1</li><li>62.7</li><li>27.3</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}={64}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}-{64}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{17}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{17}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4.1231056256177}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4.1}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{62.733955549281}\approx{62.7}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{9}}\right)}}}\approx{27.266044450719}\approx{27.3}</m></p>

</solution>
